{
  "stem": "27443.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At the end of the day, we were given the soup and the portion of bread.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But being that I had privilege, that David helped me with food, I was privileged to give my soup to some friends, that they need it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I brought, every night after work, to a friend of mine that lives now in Boca, here.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That she was with me in Majdanek, and in Skarzysko, [INAUDIBLE], we were liberated together.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she remembers because she had a very bad infection.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Was giving up, not to live.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I brought her, every night, my portion of soup, into the back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And David was my friend till they evacuated Skarzysko.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When they started evacuating Skarzysko, his brother that used to work with the doctors at that time for the camp, came to ask me that David shouldn't go into transport with me.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because David insisted that he wants to go into transport with me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We didn't know where we were really going again.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We didn't know that we are going to another [? hassock. ?] But he begged me that because he wants his brother to go with him.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because the ones that they worked with the doctors were going with the next transport.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They didn't know where they were going either, but he wanted his brother to be with him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But David insisted that he wanted to go with me in transport.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So he did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He went with me to Tschenstochau, which was a very fatal move, because his brother went to Buchenwald, but he remained alive.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He lives now in Haifa, and I visited him in Israel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But David, unfortunately, on the day that I was liberated, they evacuated, again, the camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
